- "captains steering their ships" metaphorically refers to coaches leading their teams;
- "sailing beyond their rivals" metaphorically represents winning against the opposing teams;
- "waters of competition" is a metaphor for the context of games or matches.

- 'maestros' refers to the coaches;
- 'orchestras' metaphorically represent the teams under their leadership;
- 'struck up a symphony of more than a century of points' means achieving an average score greater than 100 points per game.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT player_id
FROM game_statistics
WHERE assists > 0;

SELECT game_id, COUNT(DISTINCT player_id) AS unique_players
FROM game_statistics
GROUP BY game_id;
